1. What are Python's built-in data structures and when would you use each?
Data Structure	Ordered	Mutable	Use Case
List []	Yes	Yes	Dynamic collection, frequent updates
Tuple ()	Yes	No	Fixed data, dictionary keys
Set {}	No	Yes	Unique values, fast membership checks
Dictionary {k:v}	Yes (3.7+)	Yes	Key-value lookups
String	Yes	No	Text processing

Example:

users = ["John", "Mike"]      # list
coords = (10, 20)             # tuple
skills = {"python", "sql"}    # set
employee = {"id": 1}          # dict
