8. Python GIL

Global Interpreter Lock allows only one thread to execute Python bytecode at a time.

Impact
CPU-bound

No real parallelism.

threading

Often slower.

I/O-bound

Useful because threads wait for I/O.

Use multiprocessing for CPU-heavy work.

9. Threading vs Multiprocessing vs Asyncio
Feature	Threading	Multiprocessing	Asyncio
Parallel CPU	No (GIL)	Yes	No
Memory	Shared	Separate	Shared
Best For	I/O	CPU	Massive I/O

Examples:

Threading → API calls
Multiprocessing → image processing
Asyncio → thousands of websocket connections
